Analysis of the Main Target Image  
• Overall there are two “sub‐assemblies.”  
  1) A tall red rectangular “ring” with a horizontal circular hole, through which a flat green block is passed.  
  2) A “car” shape consisting of:  
     – Two orange cylinders laid horizontally (the wheels/axles).  
     – A yellow rectangular block resting on those cylinders (the car’s body).  
     – A blue cube on top of the left side of the yellow block.  
     – A yellow half‐cylinder on top of the right side of the yellow block.  

• Layering and Counts  
  – The red/green ring assembly effectively has two blocks in one layer (the green block passes through the red ring).  
  – The car assembly has three vertical layers:  
    1) The two orange wheels on the bottom.  
    2) One yellow rectangular block spanning those wheels.  
    3) A blue cube on one end of that block and a yellow half‐cylinder on the other end.  

Selecting the Required Blocks from the Dictionary  
Below is the exact block match (no rotation allowed beyond what is shown in the dictionary images):  
• Red ring block with horizontal hole → Block index 4  
• Green flat rectangular bar, oriented horizontally → Block index 8  
• Blue cube → Block index 6  
• Yellow rectangular block (short, horizontal) → Block index 11  
• Yellow half‐cylinder, flat side down → Block index 14  
• Orange cylinders (wheels), horizontally oriented → Block index 13 (used twice)  

Hence, the indices needed (with repeats as required) are:  
(4), (8), (13), (13), (11), (6), (14).  

Assembly Order  
{
  Step1: Move block with index 4,  
  Step2: Move block with index 8,  
  Step3: Move block with index 13,  
  Step4: Move block with index 13,  
  Step5: Move block with index 11,  
  Step6: Move block with index 6,  
  Step7: Move block with index 14  
}
